<div class="container">
    <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p><strong>Last Updated:</strong> January 2, 2026</p>

    <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
    <p>PatientTracker is committed to protecting the privacy and security of patient information. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, disclose, and safeguard health information in compliance with applicable healthcare privacy laws and regulations.</p>

    <h2>2. Information We Collect</h2>
    <p>We collect and maintain the following types of information:</p>
    <ul>
        <li><strong>Patient Health Information:</strong> Medical records, diagnoses, treatment plans, medications, and health history</li>
        <li><strong>Personal Information:</strong> Names, contact details, date of birth, and identification numbers</li>
        <li><strong>Clinical Data:</strong> Vital signs, lab results, imaging reports, and care notes</li>
        <li><strong>Administrative Information:</strong> Appointment schedules, billing information, and insurance details</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>3. How We Use Your Information</h2>
    <p>Patient information is used solely for:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Providing and coordinating patient care</li>
        <li>Treatment planning and clinical decision-making</li>
        <li>Communication between healthcare providers</li>
        <li>Quality improvement and safety monitoring</li>
        <li>Compliance with legal and regulatory requirements</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>4. Information Security</h2>
    <p>We implement comprehensive security measures to protect patient information, including:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Secure, encrypted data storage and transmission</li>
        <li>Access controls and user authentication</li>
        <li>Regular security audits and monitoring</li>
        <li>Staff training on privacy and security protocols</li>
        <li>Physical and technical safeguards</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Information Sharing</h2>
    <p>Patient information is only shared with:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Authorized healthcare providers involved in patient care</li>
        <li>Healthcare team members with appropriate access permissions</li>
        <li>Legal authorities when required by law</li>
    </ul>
    <p>We do not sell, rent, or share patient information with third parties for marketing purposes.</p>

    <h2>6. Patient Rights</h2>
    <p>Patients have the right to:</p>
    <ul>
        <li>Access their health information</li>
        <li>Request corrections to their records</li>
        <li>Receive an accounting of disclosures</li>
        <li>Request restrictions on certain uses or disclosures</li>
        <li>File a complaint regarding privacy practices</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>7. Data Retention</h2>
    <p>Patient records are retained in accordance with applicable healthcare regulations and legal requirements. Records are securely archived and disposed of according to established protocols.</p>

    <h2>8. Compliance</h2>
    <p>PatientTracker is designed to comply with applicable healthcare privacy regulations, including HIPAA (Health Insurance Portability and Accountability Act) and other relevant laws governing the protection of health information.</p>

    <h2>9. Changes to This Policy</h2>
    <p>We reserve the right to modify this Privacy Policy as needed to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. Updates will be posted with a revised "Last Updated" date.</p>

    <h2>10. Contact Us</h2>
    <p>If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or our privacy practices, please contact:</p>
    <p>
        <strong>Privacy Officer</strong><br />
        PatientTracker<br />
        Email: privacy@patienttracker.com<br />
    </p>

